            <p>Hebrew Sunday&#45;School Society&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia&#44; June 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#47;90<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Dr Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>I am instructed<lb/> by the Board of Managers<lb/> of the Hebrew Sunday<lb/> School Society&#44; to thank<lb/> you for being present<lb/> at the closing exercises<lb/> of the sewing schools<lb/> and lending&#44; as usual&#44;<lb/> your aid in making<lb/> the occasions agreeable<lb/> to children and all<lb/> interested.  In obeying<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the wishes of the Board<lb/> I should&#44; I know&#44; be<lb/> more &#34;official&#44; but&#44; it<lb/> seems almost a farce<lb/> to resort to the <hi rend="underline">regulation</hi><lb/> form with one so<lb/> closely identified with<lb/> the schools&#44; and for<lb/> whom we always look<lb/> in any movement<lb/> in their interest.<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping&#44; dear sir&#44;<lb/> that you will under&#45;<lb/>stand the feeling that<lb/> prompts my resorting<lb/> to this informal<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>tone&#44; I am<lb/> Yours very truly<lb/> Clara Hahn<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
